      <body>This is great, thanks for doing it. I would like to see it explain the behavior around nested transactions. The desired behavior, and I think this is what AR implements is:

- after_commit is triggered after the outermost transaction commits
- after_rollback is triggered after the transaction the record was updated/whatever in is rolled back

This behavior should also be explained in the API docs.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is great, thanks for doing it. I would like to see it
explain the behavior around nested transactions. The desired
behavior, and I think this is what AR implements is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;after_commit is triggered after the outermost transaction
commits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;after_rollback is triggered after the transaction the record
was updated/whatever in is rolled back&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This behavior should also be explained in the API docs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
